            {
              "id": "support-accordion",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "accordion",
              "settings": {
                "tabs": [
                  {
                    "tab_title": "How do I get help if I have issues?",
                    "tab_content": "<p>If you encounter any issues or have questions, you can:</p><ul><li>Check our <a href=\"https://smartpropertywidget.com/spw/Documentation.html\" target=\"_blank\">Documentation</a> for detailed guides</li><li>Contact our support team via email</li><li>Reach out through your CRM provider's support channel</li></ul><p>We're here to help you get the most out of Smart Property Widget!</p>",
                    "_id": "support-1"
                  },
                  {
                    "tab_title": "Is there documentation available?",
                    "tab_content": "<p>Yes, we provide comprehensive documentation covering all aspects of the widget. Visit our <a href=\"https://smartpropertywidget.com/spw/Documentation.html\" target=\"_blank\">Documentation page</a> for detailed guides on components, templates, configuration options, and more.</p>",
                    "_id": "support-2"
                  },
                  {
                    "tab_title": "Can I request new features?",
                    "tab_content": "<p>Absolutely! We're always looking to improve Smart Property Widget based on user feedback. If you have a feature request or suggestion, please contact our support team. We review all requests and prioritize based on user demand and feasibility.</p>",
                    "_id": "support-3"
                  },
                  {
                    "tab_title": "My properties are not showing. What should I do?",
                    "tab_content": "<p>If properties are not displaying, try these steps:</p><ul><li><strong>Check your connection:</strong> Ensure your website is properly connected to your property management system</li><li><strong>Verify property status:</strong> Make sure properties are marked as \"active\" or \"published\" in your CRM</li><li><strong>Clear cache:</strong> Clear your browser cache and any website caching plugins</li><li><strong>Check filters:</strong> Ensure no filters are accidentally limiting the results</li></ul><p>If the issue persists, contact our support team for assistance.</p>",
                    "_id": "support-4"
                  },
                  {
                    "tab_title": "How often is the widget updated?",
                    "tab_content": "<p>We regularly update Smart Property Widget with new features, improvements, and bug fixes. Updates are deployed automatically, so you always have access to the latest version without needing to do anything. Major updates are announced through our communication channels.</p>",
                    "_id": "support-5"
                  }
                ],
